name: Prim.Symbol
comments: The Prim.Symbol module is embedded in the PureScript compiler. Unlike `Prim`, it is not imported implicitly. It contains automatically solved type classes for working with `Symbols`.

declarations.comments: Compiler solved type class for appending `Symbol`s together.
declarations.title: Append

declarations.comments:
Compiler solved type class for comparing two `Symbol`s.
Produces an `Ordering`.
declarations.title: Compare

declarations.comments:
Compiler solved type class for either splitting up a symbol into its
head and tail or for combining a head and tail into a new symbol.
Requires the head to be a single character and the combined string
cannot be empty.
declarations.title: Cons
